Package: epishiny.timeline
Title: Patient Care-Pathway Timeline Module for 'epishiny'
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Hugo", "Soubrier", , "hugo.soubrier@epicentre.msf.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A standalone 'epishiny' module that draws patient care-pathway
    timelines. Each case is shown as one row of a Highcharts 'xrange' chart,
    from symptom onset to exit (recovery or death), with the health
    structures visited drawn as rectangles over the disease phase and an
    optional supposed-incubation window. The module follows the 'epishiny'
    module conventions (a 'bslib' card with a gear-toggled options panel and
    the cross-module reactive contract) so it composes alongside the core
    'epishiny' time, place and person modules. Following the module-package
    model, it does not depend on 'epishiny' itself: small helpers are mirrored
    locally so it installs without pulling in 'epishiny''s full set of
    visualisation dependencies.
